The first match with Rey/Sin vs. Damien/Cody suffers from disconnection errors from the user's Open Box AVerMedia PCIe capture card. The person capping had to disconnect the USB and the signal was lost, and lots of error messages popped up on the screen, interfering quite a bit. There's also a "Record" logo stuck in the corner for the entire thing, but it's not that intrusive at all. Source is SkySports HD, but the encoding settings for the AVC profile being used was not well-done and video suffers mass pixelation and color distortion. Resolution of video is only 400p, which is a non-traditional SD resolution. If the broadcast is HD, the SD encode should be the highest SD resolution of 480p with a bit higher bitrate. I highly suggest downloading another low quality copy or simply downloading it in 720p. Regardless, thanks for the upload and time, whoever did it. You do need a better capture card and should record the show as a base file of 720p @ 60FPS or 1080i if your card can't utilize 60FPS. Makes for smoother transitions when encoding it to 29.970FPS or below if you use a proper b-frame pyramid in your h.264 settings.
